HEADWORD: Re-argue
<hw>Re-ar"gue</hw></mhw>
<pr>(r⟦emac⟧*⟦aum⟧r"g⟦umac⟧)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <def>To argue anew
or again; <as>as, This politician will be forced into
<ex>re-arguing</ex> an old national campaign</as>. Usually used without
the hyphen.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source> + <source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Reargument</ent>⟦br⟧
